Looks good to me. All my line comments are tiny nits.

Taking into account @robertamarton's comments about privileges, and @anoopsharma00's preference for putting the view text in log files rather than the metadata TEXT table, I'm wondering if the right solution short-term is to not attempt view recreation, and instead log all views to a log file. Once the privileges issue is resolved for the drop/recreate technique, we can revisit recreating the views. Does this sound like a better approach?

It might be good to think about how alter, views, other dependencies, and
privileges all work together.  I have worked previously on a project that
kept invalid views in the metadata and then provided support to fix them
and make them valid.  I don’t have an issue with just storing invalid view
in a log somewhere for now.

```
 Roberta
```
